                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14146574" author="rohini" created="Wed, 24 Sep 2014 18:29:19 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sseth&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sseth&quot;&gt;Siddharth Seth&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;br/&gt;
   What is the reason for separate AM and Tez DAG acls? Would there be a case where you expect an AM to be launched by one user and to be used for DAG submission by others or just different DAG acls for scripts submitted from same pig/hive shell by a user? When should the DAG acl be set?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I believe for the AM, we set the TezConfiguration in TezClient. And for DAG, set it using DAG.setAccessControls(). What happens if ACL is not set? Is it view and modify for all?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14165907" author="hitesh" created="Thu, 9 Oct 2014 23:40:19 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=rohini&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;rohini&quot;&gt;Rohini Palaniswamy&lt;/a&gt; The ACLs for the AM are considered to be &quot;super-user&quot; settings i.e. anyone who is the AM ACLs list will have similar powers over all DAGs that run within that session/AM. DAG ACLs were introduced for cases such as Hive ( when using HiveServer2 ) where the AM is launched as user hive ( which is a super user ) and queries submitted by different users are run as hive within the same AM. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ACLs applied when looking at a DAG are a union of AM and DAG ACLs. Therefore if DAG ACLs are not set, only the AM ACLs will take effect. If you are translating from MR to Tez, you should only need to define the AM ACLs and not need to set DAG ACLs until you end up with a use-case similar to that of Hive.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14167291" author="rohini" created="Fri, 10 Oct 2014 19:48:31 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the clarification &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=hitesh&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;hitesh&quot;&gt;Hitesh Shah&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14167340" author="daijy" created="Fri, 10 Oct 2014 20:19:59 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14171614" author="rohini" created="Tue, 14 Oct 2014 23:07:23 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to branch-0.14 and trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
